article.headline: New Orleans 64, South Alabama 58
article.story: MOBILE, Ala. (AP) -- Bo McCalebb scored 14 of his game-high 16 points in the second half to lead New Orleans to a 64-58 victory over South Alabama in both teams' Sun Belt Conference opener Thursday night. The Jaguars (5-7, 0-1 Sun Belt) led 30-26 at halftime, and built their biggest lead, 32-26, on a Michael Phillips bucket to start the second half. But they let New Orleans (7-6, 1-0 Sun Belt) outscore them 38-28. The Privateers tied the game at 36-36 with 15:22 remaining on Victor Brown's free throw. Nathaniel Parker, who came off the bench to grab a game-best 12 rebounds, nailed a basket at the 9:54 mark to give New Orleans the lead. South Alabama got within a point on a pair of free throws by Henry Williams with 8:48 remaining, and again at 6:03 when Bedden hit two more, but New Orleans responded with six straight points to extend the lead to 55-48. The Jaguars made one last run, trimming the deficit to 58-56 with 1:19 left, but wouldn't get closer. McCalebb hit two free throws with 34 seconds left to seal the victory. The Jags were held to 33 percent shooting from the field, and a season-low 13 percent from 3-point range. UNO finished with 48 percent shooting.
